/F1 10 Tf
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 744 Tm (Q: Why use OCR?) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 702 Tm (A: Rural loan documents often exist as physical images. OCR converts those images into text that) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 688 Tm (the system can process.) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 660 Tm (Q: Can OCR detect fake documents?) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 618 Tm (A: Not by itself. OCR extracts fields and confidence. Fraud resistance comes from cross-checking) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 604 Tm (document names with income records and routing low-confidence cases to manual review.) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 576 Tm (Q: Why use alternative income?) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 534 Tm (A: Many rural borrowers do not have formal salary slips but still have income through wallets,) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 520 Tm (remittances, cooperatives, and small businesses.) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 492 Tm (Q: Why use XGBoost?) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 450 Tm (A: XGBoost works well for tabular data and is widely used for risk scoring because it is fast,) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 436 Tm (accurate, and explainable with feature contribution techniques.) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 408 Tm (Q: Why not neural networks?) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 366 Tm (A: Neural networks are better for images, text, or huge datasets. Our risk features are tabular,) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 352 Tm (so XGBoost is more practical and easier to explain.) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 324 Tm (Q: What is SHAP?) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 282 Tm (A: SHAP explains how each feature contributed to the model output. It helps convert black-box) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 268 Tm (scores into understandable reasons.) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 240 Tm (Q: Why does compliance override ML?) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 198 Tm (A: Regulations are mandatory. A high ML score cannot override KYC or policy violations.) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 170 Tm (Q: What does "Refer" mean?) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 128 Tm (A: Refer means the system needs a human loan officer to review the case. It is used for) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 114 Tm (uncertain, incomplete, or compliance-sensitive cases.) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 86 Tm (Q: Why use Swagger?) Tj
/F1 8 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 30 Tm (RinSathi Mid-Defense Handbook | Page 49) Tj
ET
